items.name: Multi-LORA 多人LORA 家庭
items.description:
G胖不会数3，AI也不会数3，所以G胖=AI（笑）

说正题：本次是针对LORA对于3人情况的测试。鉴于目前的AI确实不会数3，使用本LORA出现超生、后宫、NTR等情况，请不要惊讶，再点几下生成就行。使用本LORA可以提高产生“三人家庭”的概率，既“父母+女儿”或者“父母+儿子”，根据你使用的关键词改变。

我主要使用的是anything4.5+权重0.75。根据实际情况可以灵活调整权重。

欢迎大家测试和反馈。

This is a performance test for LORA in the case of three people. Given that current AI cannot count to three, using this LORA may result in situations such as having multiple children or affairs, so please do not be surprised and try generating a few more times. Using this LORA can increase the probability of generating a "family of three", such as "parents + daughter" or "parents + son", depending on the keywords used.

I mainly used anything4.5 with a weight of 0.75. The weight can be adjusted flexibly according to the actual situation.

Feel free to test and provide feedback.

items.name: D&D battlemaps
items.description:
D&D battlemaps

The model is trained on fantasy battlemaps, so it works the best for medieval fantasy setting but not only limited to this.

Resolution

You need to use width and height not less than resolution 1024 but you can make it larger and that works perfectly just producing bigger battlemap.

Dimensions

You can assume battlemaps dimensions as approximately 24x24 squares (120x120 feet) for normal dimensions of specific model, for example:

  • 1024x1024 generation is 24x24 battlemap

  • 1536x1024 generation is 36x24 battlemap

  • 2048x1024 generation is 48x24 battlemap

And so on.

Also sometimes square gird is visible and you can rely on this.

Prompting

Main trigger word is "Battlemap". You can try everything after this word but you can get best results generating something in medieval fantasy setting.

Two second trigger words are "Dungeon" and "Outdoor". Use the first one for closed space, usually underground (e.g. dungeons, mines, caves, castles, labyrinths, etc.) and second for open space (e.g. forest, city, sea)

Link to huggingface for 1024: https://huggingface.co/Zapper/battlemap-1024

Link to huggingface for 768: https://huggingface.co/Zapper/battlemap-768-v-10

items.name: privateRefslave - Legacy Model
items.description:
Preserving a Legacy Model.. Again

This model has literally been uploaded, removed, uploaded, removed several times now..

( I actually saved the huggingface page months ago because I had a feeling this thing would disappear :glares: -_- )

I am uploading a pruned version and leaving it here,.

Quick Notes

  • I've pruned it down to 2gigs / fp16 and validated through several prompts that the images come out identical to the original 7gig model.

  • It only exists as a SafeTensor never had a ckpt version.

I don't plan to support this, just trying to preserve this model for the community.

[From Original Documentation]

The second version of RefSlave, a merge of anime diffusion models with the goal of producing vibrant and detailed, yet painterly images by maintaining a subtle impressionistic quality. Supports Danbooru tags within prompts.

For the original 7gb refslave_v2 (Unpruned):

https://huggingface.co/Dorshu/refslaveV2_v2/blob/main/refslaveV2_v2.safetensors

Prompting / Info

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Highres fixes (of any methodology) are your friend, especially for faces

  • This thing can work with almost any prompt both simple and complex

  • EasyNegative and other anatomy fixing TI's are your friend, especially with hands


[From Original Documentation]

(Take it with a grain of salt)

Sampling Method:
  ➣ DPM++ SDE Karras  ➔  Stable Composition, details make more sense.
  ➣ DPM++ 2M Karras  ➔  Dynamic Composition, more distortions, details often don't make sense.

items.name: VladStudio Style - cute, soft brush, watercolor style of wallpapers
items.description:
What is this?

This is a textual inversion trained on selected wallpapers of legendary artists VladStudio. The style will produce soft gradient colors, black outlines around the character, and a soft brush effect of watercolor painting.

What can I create with this?

Random cute wallpapers or images for puzzle games or just add it as a style to landscapes or scenes. It doesn't work well on characters as it will try to doodle them into the style.

Honestly, the style is unpredictable but you will be able to pick 20-30% of images and some will be very interesting.

How to work with VladStudio style?

To use the style on the landscape, follow the workflow explained here.

Wallpaper creation workflow

Settings

Recommended style strength 0.5-0.8 for creative results, 1.0 for full Vlad Studio characters. Example: (vladstudio:0.8).

CFG 7-9, depending on the model. Steps 30-50 (simple graphics, so enough). Canvas size 640x360 with high-res fix of x1.8 or 2 times, your fav upscaler, and denoising strength of 0.2-0.4. When happy, upscale more for your desired HD resolution.

Positive prompt formula

8k Unity Wallpaper, (vladstudio:0.8), [X]

[X] holds the values from the X field in the StylePile extension. Feel free to add your additional style descriptor at the end ([X], volumetric light, surreal etc) if you wish, but may affect the style.

[X] Values (subject only, no descriptors):

cute wallpaper

1boy and 1girl

lonely tree, centered

multiple hearts, love, musical notes, red theme

starry night, dark blue theme

Negative prompt

use a couple of negative embeddings and negative tags from example images of your model.

For deliberate, I used:

ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, ((((ugly)))), (((duplicate))), ((morbid)), ((mutilated)),(((cross eyed))), [out of frame], extra fingers, mutated hands, extra ears, ((poorly drawn hands)), ((poorly drawn face)), (((mutation))), (((deformed))), blurry, ((bad anatomy)), (((bad proportions))), ((extra limbs)), cloned face, (((disfigured))). out of frame, ugly, extra limbs, (bad anatomy), gross proportions, (malformed limbs), ((missing arms)), ((missing legs)), (((extra arms))), (((extra legs))), mutated hands, (fused fingers), (too many fingers), (((long neck))), (((text))),(((signatures))), face cut, head cut, cropped head, jpeg artifacts, low quality, lowres, text, watermark, logo, text, letters, signature, username, words, blurry, cropped, cartoon, worst quality, split images, out of frame, duplicate, watermark, signature, frame, text

Thanks for using

Please check the review examples below, some amazing results.

This style delivers totally unpredictable and non-repeatable results, so please share your creations with us!

items.name: Aranara Generator 兰那罗生成器 | Genshin impact
items.description:
生成自己想象中的兰那罗吧！

Generate your own imaginary Aranara!

tag: "1 lannaluo"或者"Aranara"均可触发，两触发词同时使用会导致画面出现多个兰那罗。用颜色tag来确定兰那罗的主题色，使用leaf, smile等tag或许能帮助生成兰那罗。

基于anything4.5模型进行训练，在CounterfeitV25等二次元模型均可使用，在真实系模型中可能出现蔬菜成精的效果。推荐强度~0.9。建议使用512×512尺寸，其他尺寸未经测试，我不太确定使用效果。

在使用anything4.5与CounterfeitV2模型时与其他风格化lora、角色lora均适应良好，可混合使用，产生不同艺术风格的兰那罗或者不同角色兰那罗化后的样貌。建议同时使用时，其他风格化lora权重最高不要高于0.7，过高可能无法产生兰那罗。在无法产生兰那罗时，这个lora倾向于为角色周边增添森林场景与一些植物。

在pastelMixStylizedAnime、meinapastel模型中混合其他角色lora使用时会导致兰那罗形象出现概率降低，在负面tag中加入1girl、human 或可改善，但仍会出现此问题。

tag样例——例图中神里绫华兰那罗所用tag:

1 lannaluo, kamisato ayaka (flawless radiance), ponytail, kote, blunt bangs, hair ribbon, light blue hair, smile, leaf, <lora:lannaluo-000012:0.9> <lora:kamisatoAyakaSpringbloom_v10:0.6>
Negative prompt: EasyNegative
Steps: 20, Sampler: Euler a, CFG scale: 10, Seed: 531460020, Size: 512x512, Model hash: a074b8864e, Model: CounterfeitV25_25, Clip skip: 2, ENSD: 31337

Trigger Words：use "1 lannaluo"or"Aranara" as the Trigger Word. Using both of them may cause multiple Aranaras to appear in the picture. Use color tags to determine the main color of the Aranara, and use tags such as leaf, smile may help to generate Aranara.

Training based on the anything4.5 model, can be used in 2D style models such as CounterfeitV25, and the effect of Vegetable monsters may occur in the Realistic style model. Recommend strenth: ~0.9.The 512×512 picture size is recommended.

When using the Anything 4.5 and Counterfeit V2 models, they are well adapted to other stylized lora and character lora, and can be mixed to produce different art styles of Aranara or different Aranara characters. It is recommended that when used at the same time, the weight of other stylized LoRa should not be higher than 0.7, and too high may not produce Aranara. When Aranara is not spawned, this lora tends to add a forest scene and some plants to the character's surroundings.

Mixing other characters lora in the pastelMixStylizedAnime, meinapastel model causes the Aranara image to appear less likely, and adding 1girl, human to the negative tag may be improved, but this problem still occurs.

tag example - the tag used by Kamisato Ayaka Aranara in the example picture:

1 lannaluo, kamisato ayaka (flawless radiance), ponytail, kote, blunt bangs, hair ribbon, light blue hair, smile, leaf, <lora:lannaluo-000012:0.9> <lora:kamisatoAyakaSpringbloom_v10:0.6>
Negative prompt: EasyNegative
Steps: 20, Sampler: Euler a, CFG scale: 10, Seed: 531460020, Size: 512x512, Model hash: a074b8864e, Model: CounterfeitV25_25, Clip skip: 2, ENSD: 31337

本模型使用《原神》游戏截图、《原神》官方网页活动截图与部分网图进行训练，lora所生成图片不具备任何版权，不能用于任何商业活动。This model is trained using screenshots of Genshin impacts games, screenshots of official website activities of Genshin and some network pictures. The images generated by this LoRA are not copyrighted and cannot be used for any commercial activity.

items.name: Dragon Inn
items.description:
更新人物小传，具体可看评论

I hope the model will inspire artists and enthusiasts to create unique and beautiful artwork in the New Dragon Inn style. If you are satisfied with this model, please consider supporting my work by leaving a positive review or buying me a cup of coffee.

I am excited to share my latest AI drawing model, inspired by the iconic film New Dragon Inn. This model is designed to enable artists and enthusiasts to create artwork in the distinctive style of the film.

The New Dragon Inn model is based on SD1.5. The model can be used to generate high-quality images that capture the mood and atmosphere of the film, with its bold use of colors, dramatic lighting, and intricate details.

The image size for this model is 540x300, but it can also be used to generate images in other standard sizes.

Moreover, the model includes several control parameters that allow users to adjust the generated image's atmosphere. By adjusting parameters such as coat, sand, fire, and others, users can create images that convey a variety of moods, from peaceful and serene to intense and dramatic. These control parameters provide even greater flexibility for artists and enthusiasts to experiment and create unique artworks in the New Dragon Inn style.

画师ミコジン(mikozin)的风格。使用了126张进行训练。

原训练在anythingv4.5上进行。在AOM3等其他一些checkpoint上表现也不错，但想尽可能还原画风还是在anythingv4.5上好点，推荐权重0.6-1.

The style of the painter ミコジン (mikozin). 126 sheets were used for training.

The original training was on Anythingv4.5. It also performs well on some other checkpoints such as AOM3, but if you want to restore the art style as much as possible, it is better to be on anythingv4.5, and the recommended weight is 0.6-1.

items.name: Hu Tao (Genshin Impact)
items.description:
LoRA

A LoRA for Hu Tao from Genshin Impact. This LoRA may also be able to yield results with Boo Tao.

All sample images are generated with my custom merged model UmbraMix

Prompts

  • Positive prompts should have a minimum of details about the character. Even if hu tao \(genshin impact\) is the main trigger word, when used by itself may produce unwanted results.

  • Negative prompts should be as simple as possible such as (worst quality, low quality:1.4), (blurry:1.4).

  • All sample prompts are generate with a CLIP SKIP value of 2

Weights

I recommend using the fallowing weights:

  • Closest to the character : 0.85 ~ 1.0

  • When trying to add / change the character clothing/assets : 0.5~0.75

items.name: Cupless | Crotchless - LoHa
items.description:
Please check out my Ko-Fi page if you are interested in supporting me.

LoRA commissions open! -> Fiverr

This is a LoHa LoRA! You need the extension! Why? They do a lot better with multi-concepts.
Trigger words for V1.20:

<lora:CuplessCrotchless120:0.8>(bra, cupless bra, crotchless panties)

Specifying: "pussy", "nipples", "panties", "bra" helps it with generating the actual keywords for the LoRA. If you get full panties, specify pussy for example. If you get just a "shelf bra" then specifying "bra" helps it draw the upper part...

Don't want both at the same time? Go with just "panties" or just "bra" without "nipples" or "pussy".

You can try "micro bra", "pearl thong", "nursing bra" and "string panties", "string bra". I tagged for those in the dataset BUT HAD NO LUCK with generating them (they COULD work, but not guaranteed)! Maybe for a next update.

Follow the steps in the Model Version notes to reproduce my images.

Sample images generated with Hassaku.

All negative embeds should be easy to find. and Prompts should be included in the sample images! Click the little icon in the bottom right to see it.

It learned pretty well how to do covered nipples! Probably capable of using it for any type of shirt if you just want nipples texture.
Could use same tags in negatives to control how it generates.

It was trained on 185 512x512 images scraped from the internet and 20 epochs using animefull_final_pruned.

Danbooru tags generated by Waifu Diffusion 1.4 Tagger and fine tuned for specific details like nipples texture, see-through, and impossible shirt or form fitting.

modelVersions.name: v1.20
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.6-1 like this: <lora:CuplessCrotchlessv120:0.8>.

I've used 0.8 in all samples. Haven't really tested other numbers.


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps, 512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.4, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

If anyone is curious about my version names: v{version}.{trainingEpochs}

modelVersions.name: v1.25
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.6-1 like this: <lora:CuplessCrotchlessv125:0.8>.


This version is here mostly for me, as a way to save it. Feel free to try it but I recommend using V1.20, there's literally no improvement from going over 20 epochs.


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps, 512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.4, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

Gakuran

This one goes to @dita who's a gallant supporter and asked for a gakuran model.

This model is best used along with BEKO'S IKEMEN WORLD, get it if you haven't already!

LoRA for Gadget Hackwrench, character from "Chip 'n Dale: Rescue Rangers". Can produce both SFW and NSFW images, works with other LoRAs.

  1. Use with weights 0.8 - 1.0 for more cartoonish look. Also add gh_original, simple style, cartoon style, anime to prompt and realism, realistic, photo, 3d render to negatives.

  2. Use with weights 0.6 - 0.8 for more stylized look (depending on the used model) and more flexibility.

  3. If the facial features are lacking, add mouse ears, snout to prompt (this happens sometimes with lower weights). Also, sometimes adding colored skin to negative can be useful.

V0.1:

Trained on AOM, also works with Anything and Lawlas. My first LoRA, so it can have some troubles, like generating tail. I suggest generating a smaller image and using highres.fix/img2img. All example images are generated in one run though.

Tips:

  1. To generate classic outfit, use gh_clothes, jumpsuit, long sleeves. Can also be used on other characters.

  2. gh_goggles works sometimes. Better use with goggles, goggles on head, or add to negative.

  3. Lawlas's mix most of the time generates wolf-like faces, use wolf, canine, fox, dog for negative.

  2. Input the output into another KSampler (preferably AOM2Hard) and set the second LoRA strength to 0.4. (The example images provided were created using this method.)

Recommended VAEs are AOM2Hard and vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.

items.name: Toyota Celica GT-Four ST205
items.description:
https://t.me/stdif_kos

The Toyota Celica GT-Four is a high performance model of the Celica Liftback that was produced from 1986 to 1999, with a turbocharged 3S-GTE engine, and full-time AWD. It was created to compete in the World Rally Championship, whose regulations dictate that a manufacturer must build road-going versions of the vehicle in sufficient numbers. These vehicles are referred to as "homologation special vehicles".

The Celica GT-Four came in three generations; the ST165, based on the fourth generation Celica, and manufactured between October 1986 and August 1989; the "super round" shape ST185 produced from September 1989 to September 1993; and the ST205, built from February 1994 to June 1999.

The Celica GT-Four production cars were built at Toyota's Tahara plant in Aichi Prefecture, Japan, and the rally cars were prepared by Toyota Team Europe in Cologne, Germany.

The Celica GT-Four ST165 made its World Rally Championship (WRC) debut in the 1988 Tour de Corse, with its first WRC victory coming in the 1989 Rally Australia. The ST185's WRC debut was in the 1992 Rally Monte Carlo, and its first WRC win was in the 1992 Safari Rally, which was one of its four victories in that year. The ST185 is Toyota's most successful rally car. It won the WRC Drivers' Championship in 1992, and the WRC Manufacturers' and Drivers' championships in 1993 and 1994. The ST205 came in late 1994, and became the official rally car in 1995 with one WRC victory. It also won the 1996 European Rally Championship.

The significance of the Toyota Celica GT-Four in WRC history, previously dominated by European manufacturers, is that it was the first time a Japanese car manufacturer entered the WRC with an AWD turbocharged car, took trophies and won the titles. Since then other Japanese manufacturers have been successful in the WRC. Toyota preceded the Mitsubishi (Lancer Evolution and Galant VR-4) and the Subaru (Legacy and Impreza), but not the Mazda (Mazda 323GT-R & 323GT-X). Toyota later exited the WRC to concentrate their racing efforts in Formula One, but in 2017, 11 years after the Celica was discontinued, Toyota returned to WRC with the Toyota Yaris.

Toyota Team Europe (TTE) was also the first to introduce the anti-lag system (ALS) in their Group A ST205 Celica GT-Four rally cars, a technological breakthrough that was later adopted by other teams.
